  "disease_descriptions": {
    "Malaria": "A mosquito-borne disease caused by Plasmodium parasites. Common in tropical regions of India. Treatable with antimalarial drugs.",
    "Dengue Fever": "A viral infection spread by Aedes mosquitoes. Can range from mild to severe. Requires medical monitoring and supportive care.",
    "Typhoid": "A bacterial infection caused by Salmonella typhi, spread through contaminated food and water. Requires antibiotic treatment.",
    "Tuberculosis": "A bacterial lung disease caused by Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Highly treatable with a 6-month antibiotic course under DOTS programme.",
    "COVID-19": "A viral respiratory illness caused by SARS-CoV-2. Symptoms range from mild to severe. Consult a doctor if breathlessness develops.",
    "Chickenpox": "A highly contagious viral infection causing itchy blisters. Usually mild in children; can be severe in adults.",
    "Pneumonia": "Infection causing inflammation in the lungs. Can be bacterial or viral. Requires medical treatment.",
    "Hepatitis A": "A liver infection caused by the Hepatitis A virus, spread through contaminated food and water. Usually resolves on its own.",
    "Hepatitis B": "A serious liver infection caused by the Hepatitis B virus. Can become chronic and lead to liver damage.",
    "Cholera": "A severe bacterial infection causing profuse watery diarrhoea and dehydration. Requires immediate rehydration therapy.",
    "Influenza": "A seasonal viral respiratory illness. Rest, fluids, and antiviral drugs help recovery.",
    "Chikungunya": "A mosquito-borne viral disease causing severe joint pain. Supportive treatment relieves symptoms.",
    "Diabetes": "A metabolic condition where the body cannot regulate blood sugar. Requires lifestyle changes and medication.",
    "Hypertension": "Persistently high blood pressure. Often called the silent killer. Controlled with medication and lifestyle changes.",
    "Hypothyroidism": "Underactive thyroid gland producing insufficient hormones. Managed with daily thyroid hormone replacement.",
    "Hyperthyroidism": "Overactive thyroid gland. Treated with medications, radioactive iodine, or surgery.",
    "Gastroenteritis": "Inflammation of the stomach and intestines, usually from infection. Rehydration and rest are key.",
    "Jaundice": "Yellowing of skin and eyes due to excess bilirubin. Often a symptom of liver or bile duct problems.",
    "Peptic Ulcer": "Sores in the lining of the stomach or small intestine. Treated with antacids and antibiotics.",
    "Irritable Bowel Syndrome": "A chronic digestive disorder causing abdominal pain and altered bowel habits. Managed with diet and stress reduction.",
    "Asthma": "A chronic respiratory condition causing airway inflammation and breathing difficulty. Inhalers provide relief.",
    "COPD": "A chronic inflammatory lung disease causing obstructed airflow. Smoking is the primary cause. Requires ongoing management.",
    "Bronchitis": "Inflammation of the bronchial tubes. Acute bronchitis usually resolves; chronic bronchitis requires ongoing care.",
    "Migraine": "A neurological condition causing intense recurring headaches. Medication and lifestyle changes help.",
    "Vertigo": "A sensation of dizziness and spinning. Often caused by inner ear problems. Usually treatable.",
    "Epilepsy": "A neurological disorder causing recurrent seizures. Managed with anti-epileptic medications.",
    "Common Cold": "A viral upper respiratory infection. Rest, fluids, and OTC remedies provide relief.",
    "Urinary Tract Infection": "A bacterial infection of the urinary system. Treated with antibiotics.",
    "Anemia": "Low haemoglobin levels in the blood. Treated with iron supplements or addressing the underlying cause.",
    "Allergy": "An immune response to a harmless substance. Managed with antihistamines and avoiding triggers.",
    "Dengue Hemorrhagic Fever": "A severe form of dengue causing bleeding and organ damage. Requires immediate hospitalisation.",
    "Leptospirosis": "A bacterial infection spread through animal urine. Treatable with antibiotics.",
    "Kala-Azar": "A parasitic disease transmitted by sandfly bites, common in Bihar, Jharkhand, and UP. Requires specialised treatment.",
    "Japanese Encephalitis": "A viral brain infection spread by mosquitoes. Preventable by vaccination.",
    "Myocardial Infarction": "A heart attack. Blockage of blood supply to the heart. CALL EMERGENCY SERVICES IMMEDIATELY.",
    "Stroke": "A brain attack caused by blocked or ruptured blood vessels. CALL EMERGENCY SERVICES IMMEDIATELY.",
    "Kidney Disease": "Reduced kidney function. Requires ongoing management to slow progression.",
    "Liver Cirrhosis": "Scarring of the liver from long-term damage. Requires medical management.",
    "Psoriasis": "A chronic skin condition causing red, scaly patches. Managed with topical and systemic treatments.",
    "Eczema": "A condition causing inflamed, itchy skin. Managed with moisturisers and topical steroids.",
    "Appendicitis": "Inflammation of the appendix requiring immediate surgical removal. SEEK EMERGENCY CARE.",
    "Meningitis": "Inflammation of the brain and spinal cord membranes. SEEK EMERGENCY CARE IMMEDIATELY."
